{"title":"Breakfast Bowl Recipes to Get Egg-cited About!","slug":"breakfast-bowl-recipes-to-get-egg-cited-about","date":"2020-07-10T16:14:38","author":"Chino Valley Ranchers","content":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are only so many times you can have oatmeal or cereal for breakfast before you start craving a change. If you’re ready for an egg-citing take on breakfast, we’ve got a few breakfast bowls for you to try out.</span><!--more--></p>\n<p><b>Guacamole and Egg Breakfast Bowl</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This mouthwatering breakfast calls for spinach, toast, sour cream, avocado and sweet chilli sauce. Start by boiling one egg. Then, mash the guacamole ingredients together. And finally, place the spinach in a bowl, add the guacamole, egg, slices of red onion, cubed toast, some sour cream, sweet chilli sauce and a sprinkle of salt and pepper. And there you have it — a breakfast bowl in just 10 minutes!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the </span><a href=\"https://www.yummly.com/recipe/Guacamole-_-Egg-Breakfast-Bowl-1363420#directions\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">full recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on Yummly.</span></p>\n<p><b>Protein Breakfast Bowl</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you’re in the mood for a savory, protein-packed breakfast, then this bowl’s for you. You’ll need an onion, mushrooms, ground beef, smoked paprika, eggs, an avocado, black olives and some salt and peper. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Check out the full recipe </span><a href=\"https://www.doctoroz.com/recipe/protein-breakfast-bowl?\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>Veggie Egg Breakfast Bowl</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If cooking breakfast is just not something you can handle at 7 a.m. then we’ve got the simplest breakfast bowl you could possibly dream of. All you need are four eggs, two tablespoons of milk, a few vegies, shredded cheese and some salt and pepper. The directions are so simple you should be able to do this in your sleep!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">View the </span><a href=\"https://www.yummly.com/recipe/Veggie-Egg-Breakfast-Bowl-2194846#directions\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">full recipe</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on Yummly.</span></p>\n<p><b>Tofu Jammy Egg Breakfast Bowl</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This recipe is for the chefs out there. The list of ingredients includes white rice, chicken stock, large eggs, butter, baby spinach, green onions (or scallions), ginger, sesame oil, mirin, garlic and herb tofu, pea shoots and sesame seeds. Once you’ve gone through all the steps to prepare it, the results should be irresistible! </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Check out the full recipe on </span><a href=\"https://healthfullyeverafter.co/food-nutrition-recipe-blog/2018/tofu-jammy-egg-breakfast-protein-bowl\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Healthfuly Ever After</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<p><b>Mexican Scrambled Egg Breakfast Bowl</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This recipe checks all the boxes: veggies, protein and healthy fats. This recipe calls for bacon, red potatoes, olive oil, baby spinach, red bell pepper, onion, eggs, milk, cilantro and flour tortillas. Put this all together, and your taste buds will have their own Mexican fiesta!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Visit </span><a href=\"http://thecharmingdetroiter.com/mexican-scrambled-egg-breakfast-bowls/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Charming Detroiter</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for the full recipe.</span></p>\n"}